\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unfortunately, 
\change_deleted 267031586 1693580207
 
\change_unchanged

\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\bubeta}_{GLS}$
\end_inset

, like 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\bubeta}_{OLS}$
\end_inset

, is linear in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{\mathbf{y}}$
\end_inset

, and GLS therefore inherits OLS's primary failing – it is not robust to
 the presence of even a single outlier.
 In addition, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{\mathbf{C}}$
\end_inset

 is usually not known, and must be estimated from data.
 The estimation process is inherently noisy, and widens the distribution
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\bubeta}_{GLS}$
\end_inset

, eroding much of the theoretical advantage of GLS over WLS and OLS.
